=Kathlyn Maurean Liscomb=
Professor of Chinese Art, Art Theory, and Historiography at the University of Victoria
==Publications==
===PhD Dissertation===
* Early Ming Painters: Predecessors and Elders of Shen Chou (1427-1509). University of Chicago, 1984
===Monographs===
* Learning From Mount Hua : A Chinese Physician's Illustrated Travel Record And Painting Theory. Cambridge University Press, 1993
===Articles===
* "Wang Fu's Contribution to the Formation of a New Painting Style in the Ming Dynasty." Artibus Asiae, Volume 48, No. 1/2, 1987, pp. 39-78
* "'The Eight Views of Beijing': Politics in Literati Art." Artibus Asiae, Volume 49, No. 1/2, 1988-1989, pp. 127-152
* "The Role of Leading Court Officials as Patrons of Painting in the Fifteenth Century." Ming Studies, No. 27, 1989, pp. 34-62
* "Before Orthodoxy, Du Qiong's (1397-1474) Art-Historical Poem." Oriental Art, Volume 37, 1991, pp. 97-108
* "A Physician's Defense of his Incurable Obsession with Painting: Wang Lü's Preface to his Painting Models Album." RES: Anthropology and Aesthetics, Volume 21,1992, pp. 26-36
* "Shen Zhou's Collection of Early Ming Paintings and the Origins of the Wu School's Eclectic Revivalism." Artibus Asiae, Volume 52, No. 3/4, 1992, pp. 215-254
* "The Power of Quiet Sitting at Night: Shen Zhou's(1427-1509) Night Vigil," Monumenta Serica, Volume 43, 1995, pp. 381-403
* "Social Status and Art Collecting: A Comparison of the Collections of Shen Zhou and Wang Zhen." The Art Bulletin, Volume 78, 1996, pp. 111-136
* "Li Bai, a Hero Among Poets, in the Visual, Dramatic, and Literary Arts of China." The Art Bulletin, Volume 81, 1999, pp. 354-389
* "Foregrounding the Symbiosis of Power. A rhetorical strategy in some Chinese commemorative art.” Art History, Volume 25, No. 2, 2002, pp. 135-161
* "Iconic Events Illuminating the Immortality of Li Bai.” Monumenta Serica, Volume 54, 2006, pp. 75-118